me1200MstpMib.name: me1200MstpMib

revisions.description: Change VLAN ID range specification from (0..4094) to (1..4095)
Definition of type InterfaceIndex changed from Unsigned32 to Integer32 as it is used as index in some tables
Do no use Unsigned32 for indexes

me1200MstpMib.description: This is a private version of the 802.1Q-2005 MSTP MIB

ME1200MSTPForceVersion.name: ME1200MSTPForceVersion
ME1200MSTPForceVersion.description: This enumeration control the STP protocol variant to run.

ME1200Point2Point.name: ME1200Point2Point
ME1200Point2Point.description: This enumeration describe the values of adminPointToPointMAC and operPointToPointMAC parameters. (Full duplex port administrative and operational status.) See 6.4.3 of IEEE Std 802.1D.

ME1200PortState.name: ME1200PortState
ME1200PortState.description: This enumeration describe the forwarding state of an interface.

me1200MstpBridgeParamsBridgeHelloTime.name: me1200MstpBridgeParamsBridgeHelloTime
me1200MstpBridgeParamsBridgeHelloTime.description: Bridge Hello Time, 13.25.7 of IEEE-802.1Q-2005. Fixed value of two seconds by the standard, but this implementation allow a compatibility range from 1 to 2 seconds, in stipulated in 802.1Q-2005

me1200MstpBridgeParamsForceVersion.name: me1200MstpBridgeParamsForceVersion
me1200MstpBridgeParamsForceVersion.description: value of the Force Protocol Version parameter - 13.6.2 of IEEE-802.1Q-2005

me1200MstpBridgeParamsBpduFiltering.name: me1200MstpBridgeParamsBpduFiltering
me1200MstpBridgeParamsBpduFiltering.description: BPDU filtering for edge ports. Control whether a port explicitly configured as Edge will transmit and receive BPDUs

me1200MstpBridgeParamsBpduGuard.name: me1200MstpBridgeParamsBpduGuard
me1200MstpBridgeParamsBpduGuard.description: BPDU guard for edge ports. Control whether a port explicitly configured as Edge will disable itself upon reception of a BPDU. The port will enter the error-disabled state, and will be removed from the active topology.

me1200MstpBridgeParamsErrorRecoveryDelay.name: me1200MstpBridgeParamsErrorRecoveryDelay
me1200MstpBridgeParamsErrorRecoveryDelay.description: The number of seconds until a STP inconsistent port is recovered. Valid values are zero (recovery disabled) or between 30 and 86400 (24 hours)

me1200MstpMstiParamTable.name: me1200MstpMstiParamTable
me1200MstpMstiParamTable.description: This is a table of the bridge instance (MSTIs) parameters

me1200MstpMstiParamEntry.name: me1200MstpMstiParamEntry
me1200MstpMstiParamEntry.description: Each MSTI has a set of parameters

me1200MstpMstiParamInstance.name: me1200MstpMstiParamInstance
me1200MstpMstiParamInstance.description: Bridge instance number. The CIST = 0, MSTI1 = 1, etc

me1200MstpMstiConfigTable.name: me1200MstpMstiConfigTable
me1200MstpMstiConfigTable.description: This is the 802.1Q - 8.9 MST Configuration table For the purposes of calculating the Configuration Digest, the MST Configuration Table is considered to contain 4096 consecutive single octet elements, where each element of the table (with the exception of the first and last) contains an MSTID value.

me1200MstpMstiConfigEntry.name: me1200MstpMstiConfigEntry
me1200MstpMstiConfigEntry.description: The first element of the table contains the value 0, the second element the MSTID value corresponding to VID 1, the third element the MSTID value corresponding to VID 2, and so on, with the next to last element of the table containing the MSTID value corresponding to VID 4094, and the last element containing the value 0.

me1200MstpMstiConfigMstid.name: me1200MstpMstiConfigMstid
me1200MstpMstiConfigMstid.description: The MSTID value associated with the vlan id

me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamTable.name: me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamTable
me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamTable.description: This is a table of the CIST physical interface parameters

me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamEntry.name: me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamEntry
me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamEntry.description: Each CIST physical interface has a set of parameters

me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamEnable.name: me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamEnable
me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamEnable.description: Control whether port is controlled by xSTP. If disabled, the port forwarding state follow the MAC state

me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamBpduGuard.name: me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamBpduGuard
me1200MstpCistInterfaceParamBpduGuard.description: If enabled, causes the port to disable itself upon receiving valid BPDU's. Contrary to the similar bridge setting, the port Edge status does not effect this setting. A port entering error-disabled state due to this setting is subject to the bridge ErrorRecoveryDelay setting as well

me1200MstpAggrParamsEnable.name: me1200MstpAggrParamsEnable
me1200MstpAggrParamsEnable.description: Control whether port is controlled by xSTP. If disabled, the port forwarding state follow the MAC state

me1200MstpAggrParamsBpduGuard.name: me1200MstpAggrParamsBpduGuard
me1200MstpAggrParamsBpduGuard.description: If enabled, causes the port to disable itself upon receiving valid BPDU's. Contrary to the similar bridge setting, the port Edge status does not effect this setting. A port entering error-disabled state due to this setting is subject to the bridge ErrorRecoveryDelay setting as well
